column5: ok I was just checking the sat map of the area for ice  http://coastwatch.glerl.noaa.gov/modis/mod...on=g&page=1      there wasn't any so I added some....one can dream can't one
after reading your post i was like "their can't be" i funny how i still clicked to see anyway.
He got me too. Should have done the whole lake.
Just wander how many people will come on the weekend with ice fishing gear to fish Cooks Bay
Terry, meet me at Minits.Looks pretty safe to me.LOL  Maybe snow for saturday,but still no cold.Out west is getting the cold temps.
ok misfish, I'll be there   I hope everyone does figure it out that I was kidding I gave the real link to the website that has them and they are up to date
Sorry Terry, too late Clouds rolled in and you see nothing
AHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHH 14C and 24" of solid ice. Perfect ice fishing weather!
lol but wait till friday..she will be making ice
Terry,Misfish bring your float tubes bud LOL. let me know how you made out  Steve
After that beauty trout you got last year I guess it's ok to dream about the ice out there.  Mike

I was there last Friday and launched out of Harry's Marina in Keswick. There was ice covering the whole channel from Harry's to the mouth of the lake.  About 1/2 inch thick in some spots, so it won't be long till there is ice!!!

I doubt that ice is there anymore Bcrdi911. 10C all day...rain...16 tomorrow..rain...rain Wed and Thur.  -30C in Northern Alberta with 2' + of snow according to the wife's cousin today. Nasty sheeet for working the rigs and makin ice up there.
Temps are definitely too warm for ice, but yes, one can dream.  It'll be here in no time.
